### 1494.

Mondino says that the muscles which raise the toes are in the outward
side of the thigh, and he adds that there are no muscles in the back
\[upper side\] of the feet, because nature desired to make them light,
so as to move with ease; and if they had been fleshy they would be
heavier; and here experience shows ...  <span
id="fr_529"></span>[829](#fn_529.md)

